body_html: @again4you, I meant that if you have an old version installed without that module available, you might see the error. If that is the case, you can create and activate virtualenv before running the build. This way you can make sure system-installed TF does not get picked up by the import in create_python_api.py.

body: @again4you, I meant that if you have an old version installed without that module available, you might see the error. If that is the case, you can create and activate virtualenv before running the build. This way you can make sure system-installed TF does not get picked up by the import in create_python_api.py.
